# Cursor AI Rules — Health Landing Page

## Project Overview
Next.js 15 + React 19 + TypeScript health assessment landing page with:
- Interactive quiz flow (multi-step questionnaire)
- Redux Toolkit state management
- React Query for server state
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- i18next internationalization (EN + FR)
- Cypress E2E and component testing
- Sentry error tracking + LogRocket session replay

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript 5.7
- Redux Toolkit 2.5, React Query 5.64
- Tailwind CSS 3.4 + Tailwind Forms + Tailwind Typography
- i18next 24 + react-i18next 15
- Cypress 13 + cypress-axe (accessibility)
- Sentry 8 + LogRocket 9

## Code Conventions
- Components: `FunctionComponent` type, default exports
- State: Redux Toolkit slices in `src/features/`
- i18n: keys in `public/locales/{en,fr}/`, use `useTranslation()` hook
- Types: interfaces in `src/types/`
- Imports: `@/` path alias resolves to `src/`
- Barrel exports: `index.ts` in each component/feature folder

## File Structure Rules
- Each component in its own folder with `.tsx` + optional `.css`
- Sub-components nested within parent folder
- Barrel exports (`index.ts`) for multi-file modules

## Commands
- `npm run dev` — dev server (turbopack, port 3000)
- `npm run build` — production build
- `npm run lint` — ESLint (flat config v9)
- `npm run format` — Prettier
- `npm run type-check` — TypeScript
- `npm run cypress:open` — Cypress GUI
- `npm run cypress:run` — Cypress headless
- `npm run test` — lint + type-check + cypress

## Quality Gates
- SonarQube: `sonar-project.properties`
- Qodana: `qodana.yaml`
- ESLint flat config: `eslint.config.mjs`
- Prettier: `.prettierrc`
- EditorConfig: `.editorconfig`